2020-12-23 20:41:35] Email received from: Rebecca Lewane <takahike@mac.com>: Mr. Zagorski,
1. Bill:  the day I was checking in, I saw on line there was a price under the $69. I had . I was tempted to cancel then get the lower price as the young man said he couldn’t change the price. However, he could include the free breakfast, which he included.
When I looked at the bill, I couldn’t understand the charges so I went to the desk. The young man, the same one, was fidgety and told me he couldn’t help me. To call the 800 number. 
There was a $20. Charge and an $11.plus. I don’t have the bill in front of me, but there was 2 $10.00 charges.
So, for 1 room at $69.00 for 2 Nights comes to $190. Plus. That is almost $100. Each night. And that is not honest. 
2. I did not go to breakfast the first morning. The second morning I went only to find most of the enormous meal I ordered was not eatable. I asked for coffee, but did not get it so I bought it at Starbucks.
I also ordered a fish dinner which was not eatable, with the exception of the fries. I couldn’t reach anyone to request something else. 
Because of the pandemic, I understand that businesses are having some difficulties but I don’t think adding all the charges that were added was the way to make up for it. 
Respectfully yours,
Rebecca Lewane
157 Hendrickson Rd.
Crystal Falls, Mi.  49920

2020-12-24 07:52:54] Reply Sent: Dear Ms. Lewane,
Happy holidays and thank you for getting back to me with more details about your stay. I hope that you are feeling better and able to spend time with friends and family – safely – this holiday.
Looking at your statement, here is some information regarding the charges:
·        When you check into the hotel, we authorize your credit for your room & tax for the whole stay, plus $25.00/nightly – this is just an authorization and not a charge to your card, even if you see it pending. We are asking your bank to hold those funds in case you charge a meal back to your room……or throw a television out the window. Anything unused from the authorization is returned to you after you check-out of the hotel. We should have explained it better.
·        Your room rate with your World of Hyatt discount was $69.42/nightly without tax. In the City of Green Bay, there is both a State of Wisconsin sales tax of 5.5% ($3.82/nightly) and a City of Green Bay hospitality tax of 10% ($6.94/nightly). Unfortunately, taxes are something we cannot skirt around.
·        At our hotel, we do charge $10/nightly for parking. We have that information listed on our website and share it with you at check-in. The reason it is not included in your stay is because we have a number of guests that use Ubers/Lyfts or are locals and use city transportation.
·        The additional charge of $11.61 was from breakfast on your day of departure.
·        I sincerely apologize that your statement was not explained more clearly and I will be speaking with Gennadiy regarding how he assisted your during your stay.
In regards to the two meals you had with us, I have shared your message with our Food & Beverage Team. We must do better and be available during dining hours so that our guests can bring concerns to us and we have an opportunity to resolve them immediately. I hope that the next time you stay with us, your experience will be more positive.
Because of the confusion on your statement and the disappointment you experienced during your meals with us I am extending a refund on your account. I am waiving the $20.00 parking charges and applying a $50.00 food & beverage credit to your final bill. A total of $70.00 will be refunded back to your VISA card in 3-7 business days. Because of the holidays, it may take a bit longer.
Again, I sincerely apologize for the inconveniences you experienced during your stay. I appreciate the feedback so that we can improve our service, even during the global pandemic.
I hope you and your family have a wonderful holiday and that 2021 treats all of us better than 2020 did. We look forward to welcoming you back in the future.
Warm regards,
Paul Zagorski, Jr.
Front Office Manager

column64:
; ; ; ; ; ;I reached out the the front desk regarding the odor of marijuana filling my room. Security was quick to respond and agreed that the odor was overwhelming.  Having already unpacked and settling into my room, I was told I would be moving to the opposite corner of the floor and I should pack my things.  

At midnight I was woken to people in the room next to me being very loud.  Why are rooms being booked back to back with no one in the hotel?  Why not spread people out and leave a vacant room in between rooms?  I chose not to address the noise as I didn't want to move again.  
Being as inconvenienced as I was, even though I only reported the stench of marijuana and not the noisy neighbors, I was shocked that I was not offered any compensation for my stay.   A guest was smoking weed in the room next door to me yet I was the one that was inconvenienced.
I will definitely consider other options when staying downtown.  Thank you.  Daniel Yonke; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

2020-12-09 09:32:30] Reply Sent: Click here to respond: Dear Mr. Yonke,

Thank you for sharing your feedback with us about your recent stay.

I do apologize for the inconvenience you experienced with the room move and noisy neighbors. We did find the guest that was smoking in their room. They were 3 floors below you and the smell was coming through the air vent in the bathroom. Unfortunately, the room category that you were booked into is one of our Deluxe Suites and as we were sold out on Saturday evening due to a large group booking 5 floors of the hotel, we sadly did not have other options at the same level of room type and did not have an upgrade above where you were. I apologize if we misunderstood your concerns and if you wanted to stay in the same room. We typically offer room moves so that our housekeeping team can get into the room to ozone it as best as we can. I also apologize that we did not proactively offer any compensation. 

I have applied a $60.00 room credit and have waived your parking. There will be a credit of $79.30 coming back to your credit card and you should see that posted in 3-5 business days. 

Please do not hesitate to reach out with any questions you may have. I hope you and your family have a very happy and safe holiday season.

Sincerely,

Paul Zagorski
Front Office Manager
Hyatt Regency Green Bay
paul.zagorski@hyatt.com

2020-12-02 08:46:59] Reply Sent: Click here to respond: Good morning Mr. Anderson

Thank you for being our guest and providing feedback.  I treat all feedback as a gift and hope by doing to make Hyatt Regency Green Bay a better place for our guests.  I am very concerned by some of your comments.  Certainly most concerning is the rudeness comment.  Might you provide some additional information regarding the colleague you are referring to?   The room you booked through PriceLine included breakfast for the 3 adults the room was booked for.  (breakfast was included)  Due to Covid-19 restrictions and limiting number of people in the Sauna, Hot Tub & Steam Room, these have been closed since March and we decided in November to begin some upgrades in this area of the pool deck insuring we could keep the pool open for our guests.  

I look forward to hearing back from you.

Sincerely,

Kristine Hall
General Manager
Hyatt Regency Green Bay
kristine.hall@hyatt.com

2020-12-02 08:47:10] Alert Closed: kh (1043679); 
2020-12-02 08:48:11] Reply Sent: Click here to respond: Dear Mr. Anderson,

We appreciate you for staying with us and for sharing your feedback.

I sincerely apologize if I or my staff treated you poorly during your stay. I personally checked you in and out and I would be incredibly appreciative if you would share some further feedback on how I can improve my customer service and what I can do to train our staff and enhance the experience for our guests. It's discouraging when we hear that our guests did not enjoy their stay and it is even more disheartening to hear that we were rude. 

During your check in, I shared our welcome letter and explained it in detail about the COVID-19 policies we're following and the amenities that are currently available to our guests. Also, our front desk staff does share that our pool area is under refurbishment while going through our check-in process. While our pool is open from 10AM-10PM, due to COVID-19, our hot tub, sauna, and steam room have been closed since March. While it is disappointing for guests, it has given us an opportunity to refurbish the area for our guests once we are able to get to normal operations. We strive to keep our website up to date as well with the amenities we are currently offering. In regards to breakfast, your reservation did include breakfast. You booked our 15% Off + Breakfast rate. I shared the breakfast package letter with you at check-in as well. I apologize if I was not clear in how the breakfast package worked and where our breakfast area is located. 

I am away from the hotel on business today and tomorrow. I will be back in my office on Friday morning and will check your account folio to ensure that everything is correct. I will follow-up with you regarding your hotel bill on Friday.

I am concerned and disappointed that our staff treated you any other way than hospitable. We strive to make all of our guest's feel like part of our family at their home away from home. I am also disappointed that you and I were not able to have this conversation in person when you stopped by the desk to check out with me. I sincerely apologize that I was under the impression that you and your travel companion enjoyed your stay with us and had I known there was a problem, I would have had an opportunity to resolve your concerns. 

Please do not hesitate to reach out if you have anything else you would like to share with us.

Sincerely,

Paul Zagorski
Front Office Manager
Hyatt Regency Green Bay
paul.zagorski@hyatt.com

While our pool is open from 10AM-10PM, due to COVID-19, our hot tub, sauna, and steam room have been closed since March. While it is disappointing for guests, it has given us an opportunity to refurbish the area for our guests once we are able to get to normal operations. We strive to keep our website up to date as well with the amenities we are currently offering. In regards to breakfast, your reservation did include breakfast. You booked our 15% Off + Breakfast rate. I shared the breakfast package letter with you at check-in as well. I apologize if I was not clear in how the breakfast package worked and where our breakfast area is located. 
> 
> I am away from the hotel on business today and tomorrow. I will be back in my office on Friday morning and will check your account folio to ensure that everything is correct. I will follow-up with you regarding your hotel bill on Friday.
> 
> I am concerned and disappointed that our staff treated you any other way than hospitable. We strive to make all of our guest's feel like part of our family at their home away from home. 2020-11-21 14:32:33] Reply Sent: Click here to respond: Dear Mr. Agnew,

Thank you for sharing your feedback in our survey.

I sincerely apologize that you've experienced multiple issues with our heating and cooling system. I'm going to be real with you - our hotel was built in 1989 with a two pipe system into concrete walls. There is a cooling mode (in summer) and a heating mode (in fall and winter) that places the entire building in one of these modes. Setting your room temperature to 68* in cool mode will feel very different that 68* in heat mode. I am sorry that our Engineering Team did not come to explain how the system work and offer alternatives to making your room a comfortable temperature. We could have brought you a room fan, turned off the fans in the HVAC system so that it didn't continue warming up your room and offered other suggestions.

We do have plans for a major refurbishment once we are able to resume normal operations after Covid-19 pandemic. The hospitality industry has been decimated through the pandemic and our large projects to improve our guest's experience has had to be postponed.

If there is anything else you wish to discuss, please do not hesitate to reach out. I will be glad to assist you.

Sincerely,

Paul Zagorski

Thank you for sharing your feedback about your recent stay with us. 

I sincerely apologize that we missed an opportunity to impress you with the details of a stay. Our parking fee is in alignment with other hotels in the Downtown Green Bay area, especially on busy weekends, we want to ensure as many hotel guests are able to park in our lot before considering overflow lots. We also share your sentiment about the in-room toilets and carpets. Unfortunately, the refurbishments and renovations that were planned for this year have been pushed back due to Covid-19. The hospitality industry, like so many industries, has taken a toll because guests are travelling less. We are hoping to begin our renovation project in the later part of 2021 or early 2022 when we all get through the global pandemic and back to normal.

In regards to the breakfast sandwiches and hoppy beers, I have spoken with our Sales Team and our Food & Beverage Manager. The hockey group worked with our team at the hotel to determine the breakfast to-go bags. I'm sorry that they did not have bacon and/or sausage on the sandwiches. Our Food & Beverage team is also always looking for ways to improve what we offer guests. I hope during your next stay with us, that we have a better selection for you.

I'm glad to hear overall it was a good stay. We will work to make improvements to the guest experience. If there is anything else you wish to discuss, please do not hesitate to reach out.

column65:
While the atrium and inside look of the hotel is beautiful, I did feel as though I was Nickle and Dimed on  Parking, Early check-in, Etc. One would assume due to the Global Pandemic that your hotel is not operating at 100% occupancy and even accounting for rooms to stay vacant before being cleaned and rerented that you had a room available for early check-in without assessing a fee. 
Having spent several years running and managing Hotels in both Milwaukee and Wisconsin Dells I had higher expectations going into this stay. My reservation was initially screwed up, I called to correct this only to be told that the day had come and gone and I paid for a room on a night I never stayed. Instead of reinstating my reservation and switching the nights and offering me a complimentary night, I was booked a second room and charged full price. This is not a good business practice. Nor how I would have done things. I feel my initial complaint of this was never escalated, nor brought to the attention of anyone who could do something about this. The rooms were fine. good sitting options other than the bedroom. The bathroom was a little small for my liking, and the toilets were low to the ground and very slow when flushing. You may want to invest in new toilets. 
The bed was wonderfully comfortable as well as the pillows. the Cuibi clock and charging stations were a present surprise and a good upgrade. The tiny balcony was a great surprise and good addition I would have used it were I not staying the night of the Flood inducing rainstorm. I did like that you provided the extra big garbage bag in the room.

2020-10-22 18:40:07] Reply Sent: Click here to respond: Dear Mr. Glaser,

Thank you for your loyalty and being a Discoverist member with World of Hyatt. I appreciate you taking the time to share your feedback in our Guest Survey.

As a company, we are working hard to provide a safe environment for our guests. We have taken the recommendations from the State of Wisconsin and CDC, as well as our corporate health team, to determine what points are able to be accounted for. While we have enhanced cleaning of all of our public areas, there are still instances where it is a guest's responsibility to protect themselves outdoors. We have listened to our guests and a majority of guests have shared they have their own personal protective equipment for being out in public. From hand sanitizer, pens/pencils/keychains to press buttons or open/close doors, our guests are using their own devices for gates and exterior doors in addition to cleaning procedures we are following. 

We are also taking steps inside the hotel for your safety. In our public areas, we are cleaning high-touchpoints multiple times throughout the day, offering multiple hand sanitizer locations, and requiring masks throughout the hotel. Our employees are temperature tested daily. In our guest rooms, when guests check out, our housekeeping team has enhanced their techniques and our Executive Housekeeper has a sanitizing mist that is sprayed throughout the room. Whenever possible, we strive to let the room sit between guests. These enhanced cleaning procedures are listed on your welcome letter, as well as on our website: https://www.hyatt.com/info/global-care-and-cleanliness-commitment

Our housekeeping team is not cleaning rooms daily for overnight guests unless it is set up with our Executive Housekeeper and they are staying for longer than 5-nights. We are committed to distancing people as best we can while still providing the high level of service you expect from Hyatt. 

Overall, I am glad that your stay was a positive one. 

If there is anything else you wish to discuss, please do not hesitate to reach out. I will be glad to assist you. 

Sincerely,

Paul Zagorski
Front Office Manager
Hyatt Regency Green Bay
paul.zagorski@hyatt.com 
920.321.5080 (1421635);

There was no way for us to tell if any additional measures were in place for room cleanliness and sanitization. column77: I reviewed several hotels in the Green Bay area.  I usually stay at Marriott properties, but when I called to ask about their mask policy with those who have exemptions, they said they had no accommodations.  I called Hyatt and they said, "no problem, we have a wristband that we ask you wear to designate your status and you won't be bothered!" I was so excited to know my health and well being was a priority in Hyatt's eyes!  I have shared this with many friends and now here on TA!
column250: I chose Hyatt Regency because they honored my mask exemption, asking me to wear a wristband to designate this, so no one would give me a problem.  I wrote Marriott and told them they should follow your innovative thinking, and that they had lost my business on this trip!  I seated myself for breakfast.  I watched others be seated AFTER me and had their orders taken BEFORE me.  I walked to the podium and retrieved a menu before a server acknowledged me...  It wasn't that busy, so not sure why I wasn't given service in a timely manner.

column239: Please see previous written comments regarding the blood stain, the size of the palm of your hand, dried onto the sheet and actually on the mattress pad itself. This was not our blood stain, this was from the previous guest who stayed in the room and the sheets weren't changed out.
column250:
I'm very disappointed in the fact that the sheets were not changed on our bed after the last guest stayed in the room, 835. We discovered a dried blood stain the size of the palm of your hand in the middle of the king size bed. This would have been terrible had we found it on the FIRST night we were there, however, we didn't discover it until the 2nd night when my husband actually pulled the blankets all the way back to get into bed. The first night it went unnoticed because we got back to the room late and when we got into bed, we had the lights turned out and just got into bed on our respective sides. The 2nd night, when this discovery was made, my husband went down to the front desk to request fresh sheets. The housekeeper brought clean sheets to the room at approximately 11:00 pm and I asked if there were clean pillow cases in the plastic bag of sheets she handed me. She stated she didn't know anything about pillow cases. I told her since the sheets were never changed from the previous guest, I could only assume the pillow cases hadn't been either. The whole idea of sleeping on the sheets and pillow cases of the previous guests to stay in the room is quite unsettling. We were there for my daughter's wedding, so as you can imagine, there wasn't an option to check out and just stay somewhere else. It was, by far, the worst experience I've ever had from that perspective. Outside of the dirty sheets, and having to reuse our towels for 3 days, the staff were all very professional and courteous. We couldn't have asked for a better wedding/reception for our guests. That part was terrific! I am disappointed that the house manager never followed up regarding the dirty sheets. This is the reason we will never stay at this facility again. The incident itself was bad enough, but to not have anyone from management follow-up, is inexcusable. 
Kindest regards,
Andrea Howe

column250: I was very concerned about mask enforcement for both guests and staff. One breakfast waitress rudely argued with me in front of her manager about my request that he mask cover her nose. A housekeeper (with no mask in sight, not even worn as a necklace or headband) told me that she has just started work for the day as she attempted to enter an elevator with me. Many (maybe 50%) guests waiting for breakfast were not wearing masks and one group tended to stand in large rowdy groups in the dining room as if they were in a sports bar preCOVID-19. Finally, some guy in the elevator touched me and tried to prevent me from exiting when I objected to riding in an elevator with his nine-year-old boy who was not wearing a mask. Hotel managements needs to emphasize to all staff (front desk agents were very good in this respect) that masks must be worn properly at all times. Maybe more importantly, mask and elevator capacity rules should be emphasized to guests at check in and hotel employees should remind people whenever they notice violations.
Why the 10$(A Day!) parking fee?! If I would have know about the fee I wouldn’t have stayed there.

column77: One of the few hotel serve hot breakfast during COVID. Good location. You have to pay for parking $10 per day. Path room could be better and needs renovation. TV is limited to the channel. column250: Paul was very accommodating with giving discounts and price matching the website. He saved me $50!!!! Thanks Paul. That being said some things that can be improved... the shower was disgusting. I saw black hairs all over the wall (I’m blonde) and it seemed like it had never been cleaned before which is sad especially during a global pandemic. Another issue I had was that I was in a wedding The day of check in and was unable to pick up my keys until after midnight. I picked up my keys and headed to the brides room to package up her $1700 wedding dress which took a good chunk of time. I didn’t end up going to my room until 2:30 am. When I tried to open my door the key didn’t work. I felt very unsafe walking around by myself at 2:30 am in the morning expecting to go straight to my room when I was intoxicated (I’m of age and had a good time at my best friends wedding). I know I had a unique situation with check in but please do better next time when you accidentally assign someone the wrong room at midnight !!!!

2020-08-21 22:46:58] Email received from: Anne Freund <afreund27@gmail.com>: Dear Mr. Zagorski,
Thank you so much for responding back and letting me know why our group was split up on different floors as much as they were.  I realize you have other guests and I can see how it could be difficult to keep everybody together.  I just thought we were more together as a group in past years.  We always enjoy our time there since often times we celebrate birthdays.  This time we were celebrating a wedding, which of course included our group being able to stay here once again.  We love the way the building is designed so we can walk completely around in a circle on each floor.  And even though the elevators are slow, we still love them.  More to view while in them.  
My best friends family has been coming to this hotel for about 20 to 30 years and they always look forward to seeing Chester.  We were so happy to hear he is still there.  My best friend just happened to ride the elevator with him.  I believe I saw him but it was from a distance.  
I am sure things have changed there due to the Coronavirus but we miss the palm trees and the hut.  They made the place feel more tropical, which was especially nice since often times we would come in November.  I guess it was time for an update though.  It looks nice, just different.  
I also have to mention that the beds are wonderful.  I wish I could have brought mine home with me.  That is the best I have slept in a long time.  
Could you please do me one favor and check to see if the fan works in the bathroom of the room I was in?  I was in Room 411 and I don’t think it worked unless there is no fan, which would be strange if there wasn’t.  I forgot to mention it when checking out.  
Thank you so much!
Sincerely,
Anne.

Thank you for your loyalty to the Hyatt family of hotels and for being an Explorist. I also appreciate you sharing your thoughts with us in our guest survey.

I sincerely apologize that your experience with breakfast was not efficient and that some of our staff made it seem that they couldn't care less about our guest's experience. I assure you, I have already spoken with our Food & Beverage Leadership Team so that we can take your message and train our team to work in sync and efficiently for our guests. I have also looked at your breakfast slip and have discovered what has happened with your statement. I do see the $3.00 gratuity you left for Alicia. When the package covered your entrees, the tax ($1.27) incorrectly posted to your statement. I have taken it upon myself to double-check other guest's folios as well and it seems the issue has only affected your bill. I have forwarded your receipt to our IT Team to have that resolved. It's strange and I want to assure you, this was not something done nefariously. 

As a goodwill gesture for the inconvenience you experienced during breakfast and for the mispost on your statement, I am applying a $25.00 credit to your account. This will be refunded to your VISA credit card ending in 8449. You should see this reflected on your statement in 5-7 business days.  

Again, I sincerely apologize for the experience you had with us and appreciate you sharing your feedback with us so that we can improve moving forward. If there is anything else I can do to assist you, or if there is anything else you wish to discuss, please do not hesitate to reach out.

Warm regards,

Paul Zagorski

column250:
We were unable to use the swimming pool because there were no adult swim hours and too many kids/families in there at all times. We chose this hotel because it was downtown And had an indoor pool. We didn’t feel safe due to COVID. The pool was too over-run with bodies. There needs to be time- limits and no children after 9pm if pool closes at 10:00.

While people are waiting for breakfast or elevators there needs to be space between them. We often felt people were too close to us and there were too many guests and not enough employees to do anything   about it. 

The lower cost of room was nil by the fact that we had to pay for parking and couldn’t use the pool. Mine as well stayed somewhere else for $20 more a night. Then we would have had those ammentites we could have used and less crowds of people during COVID.

column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;Love the Hyatt in Green Bay. I made a concerted effort to choose this hotel during Covid because I was impressed with their safety policies, liked the idea of a suite in case finding dining options with take out or outdoor dining was difficult, and felt better overall about the spacious layout of this hotel.  I think that some of the materials in the hotel rooms are starting to show their wear and tear and may need replacing eventually (ie, carpeting was pulling up near the bathroom door and the bathroom shelving was pretty scratched up), but otherwise, very clean and well updated.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column250: Clear Covid policies were handed to us upon our arrival.  I appreciated that there was hand sanitizer on tables throughout the hotel and one at every elevator station.  Sometimes the hand sanitizer was missing from an individual station, perhaps just getting refilled, and maybe a replacement could be set out while backups are being refilled.

They allowed for optional masks. Thank you for allowing us to make our own decisions and not forcing draconian measures on people.  We felt cared for because we where empowered to make our own decision. Thank you!

column250: Friendly staff, room was not clean. Blood stain was found on inside of the bathroom door as well as dirty (hopefully chocolate) finger prints by light switch in kitchen area, which indicates surfaces are being skipped for cleaning. We were switched to a new room and found tooth paste was on bathroom wall by light switch and greasy finger prints in kitchen area. Stayed in this room and just disinfected surfaces myself.
When we checked out the baggage carts were all used and we waited for a half hour to get one, but gave up. Other than that it was GREAT! We really enjoyed our stay and will be back!
Don’t charge for parking. Ten dollars a day is high.

Dear Sylvia,

Thank you for taking the time to respond to our Guest Survey and share your feedback with us.

I sincerely apologize that your room keys caused undue inconvenience and that it took so many tries for them to only get one to work. As for your room request and assignment, while we do our best to accommodate guest requests, we cannot guarantee those requests. Room assignments are based on availability, typically 24-72 hours prior to arrival, and based on check-outs that take place on your day of arrival. In regards to your room rate, I will have to do more research into quotes vs. actual charges. I will be following up with you regarding your rate. Because you stayed with a wedding, if you booked through the wedding block, that is a contracted rate. That rate is locked in, compared to standard rates that can fluctuate.

I will be doing more research into your concerns. I sincerely apologize that a weekend meant for celebration was met with frustration and inconvenience. I will follow up with you by the end of the week.

If there is anything else you wish to discuss prior to my follow up, please do hesitate to reach out.

Sincerely,

column250: Upon check in I was given 2 key cards upon which neither worked. Having returned to the guest service desk 4 times from the 7 th floor only 1 ever worked. Was very disappointed and dissatisfied!! Will never stay here again!!

Per industry practice, when you arrive, we authorize the room & tax for however many nights of your stay, plus we authorize $25.00/night for an incidental/security hold. When you departed, we CHARGED that authorization $119.56 which was Room Rate + Tax + $15 Early Check-In Fee that you purchased + Parking. The initial authorization should fall off your account in 24-48 business hours depending on how fast your bank processes items for you. column205: Excellent selection of breakfast items. Probably the best breakfast buffet I've ever had
column213: I found the lunch's and dinner to be mediocre. The first lunch was a cold sandwich with a tasteless bun which I put aside and ate the contents alone. The second lunch was better with a good chicken breast but a very small serving of potatoes and five green beans. A larger serving of green beans would have been appreciated. The banquet dinner was disappointing with ordinary baby carrots and a beef stroganoff with very little beef included. But there was a tasty salad served with good dressing. Service was terrific though.

Good afternoon Ms. Villafuerte, 

Thank you for taking the time to fill out our guest satisfaction survey, and thank you for being a World of Hyatt member. We do appreciate your loyalty to Hyatt. 

We are sorry to hear about the heating issues that occurred with your guest room. We strive to provide the most comfortable stay for our guests and we are sorry we fell short with this. I will pass along the feedback to our engineering team. In the future if you do stay with us, please reach out to the front desk if you notice any issues and we will try to rectify the situation for you the best we can, with either a space heater or a room move if engineering could not resolve the issue. 

As for parking, we do have the parking fee for our guests, as we have a gate system to limit non guests from parking in our lot. At the time of your stay, they were not operational as they were still being installed and properly programmed. In the future, the ticket will need to be verified with the desk, and the parking will be charged to the room as it was for your stay. This will allow you unlimited in and out access. Otherwise you would have to pay the gate at hourly rate of $1 per hour. 

As for our shuttle, it is based on availability. It is primarily meant for airport runs only, and is recommended to have rides scheduled at least a week in advance to guarantee accommodation. We try our best accommodate any secondary ride requests, but the hours are limited.  If you do stay with us in the future and would need the shuttle, please call ahead of time or reach out to me directly, and we will be happy to accommodate. 

If you have any other questions or concerns, please feel free to reach out to me.

We hope the rest of your stay went well, and hope to see you again soon. 

Warm Regards, 

Kolton Madlem
Assistant Front Office Manager
Hyatt Regency Green Bay

Thank you for sharing your feedback on our Guest Survey.

I sincerely apologize that the television in your room was not working appropriately and that our Engineering Team and Security Team was unable to fix it. Also, I am sorry that you were not informed of the Hyatt global outage with Chromecast. We definitely had some opportunities during your stay.

In regards to parking, our parking fee is aligned with other full-service hotels in the Green Bay area. Because it was a busy weekend, we sometimes fill to capacity. Many of our guests enjoy parking in the Main Street Garage as well as the pricing is comparable and it is covered with the Skywalk to bring you into the hotel. I can understand your frustration. As a goodwill gesture for the inconveniences you experienced during your stay, I am extending 10,000 points to your World of Hyatt account. You should see the points in your account in 3-5 business days. 

Again, I sincerely apologize for the inconveniences you experienced during your stay and hope that the improvements we will make based on your feedback will make for a better stay for you and your family in the future.

column77:
I generally like Hyatt hotels, but this location had some issues that made my visit frustrating:
1) Shuttle service did not run after 10 pm, which is not too surprising. But there was no driver available to make an airport run at 11 am on my departure day - and I tried to schedule this a day in advance. That's unacceptable.
2) My room was not cleaned on the first day - I was out all day and there was no DND tag on the door. I called the front desk to report this but did not want service at night when I got to the room. The next day when I went to the room at 3:30 pm it still hadn't been cleaned. I did request housekeeping and it got done, but I felt like the staff din't really care one way or the other about this issue.
3) Many of the common spaces were dirty. A beer can sat next to an elevator for 2 days. The stairwells were filthy.
That all being said, the room was quite nice and I slept well. It's too bad the service was so erratic.

column64: ; ; ;I found a diaper under the pull out couch, disgusting; ; ;I tried to check in 2 hours after designated time and was told our rooms were not ready and offered rooms that were not suites when we paid for suites. No compensation was offered with this. Then I was charged 14$ per room because they said they just charge fees to my card on file rather than travelocity because my card was on file. Seems criminal to me. I paid in full when booking and was just given excuses why this happened. Extremely unlikely to ever return given the treatment on many scenarios during my stay. To find a diaper under the couch was absolutely disgusting. And the pull out couch was the most uncomfortable thing I have ever attempted to sleep on. Every bar was extremely pronounced and caused severe back pain.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

Everything else was fine.; ; ;The overall hotel is very impressive and for the price of the room we were very happy.  The granite countertop in our room was dirty, I know they can be difficult to clean but ours had some sticky spots.  Also I originally booked the room on they hyatt website with a code for our event.  After doing this I saw that I could get a similar rate, maybe $20 more, but it would include breakfast.  When I called the hotel I spoke with Paul who assured me that when I checked in for our stay I could speak with him and that he would get us a similar deal on breakfast.  When we checked in Paul was there but was too busy to help us. We did end up eating breakfast in the lobby and it was considerably more than the deal on Expedia.  I try to always book with the hotel directly, not third party, for better service. column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;I have stayed at your Hyatt location many-many times.  When we checked in we requested an upgrade to an executive suite which we then paid for.  After settling in we received a phone call from the front desk saying they wanted to alert us to the fact that on Sunday evening between 9:00 p.m. and 12:00 a.m. there would be some work being done outside of our bedroom windows.  It was explained that there would be no noise-perhaps only lights shining. On Sunday evening while in bed there was horrific noise - crashing, etc.  We were unable to even hear the television set at times. column65: I have stayed at your Hyatt location many-many times.  When we checked in we requested an upgrade to an executive suite which we then paid for.  After settling in we received a phone call from the front desk saying they wanted to alert us to the fact that on Sunday evening between 9:00 p.m. and 12:00 a.m. there would be some work being done outside of our bedroom windows.  It was explained that there would be no noise-perhaps only lights shining. On Sunday evening while in bed there was horrific noise - crashing, etc.  We were unable to even hear the television set at times.  We did contact the front desk and while we were offered complimentary breakfasts the next morning, which we refused, it certainly did not make our sleeping experience at all comfortable.

2020-02-11 07:35:17] Email received from: Joseph Rondinelli <jarondinelli@gmail.com>: Pavy,
It was my first visit to Green Bay and I was there for business so my experience is limited.  I didn’t know what to expect but the morning buffet exceeded my expectations.  I did have a chance to dine out while I was in Green Bay that included dinner at the Tavern in the Sky and brunch at The Cannery and both were wonderful.  Saturday night I just wanted to chill in the hotel  and I had an early flight the next morning.  
My only complaint is that under the Hyatt Brand I expected better in room or in the hotel dining options.  It was basically a $40 take out meal which seemed disproportionate for what it actually was even though I expected it to be higher.  It came from the Pub which isn’t even part of your domain?
Thank you for reaching out, I know it takes a great deal of effort to oversee dinning and events at such a large facility.  
I’m an interior designer so I will share one more observation related to food and space.  I find the seating in the lobby set up only for breakfast creates a very unwelcoming feeling when abandoned the rest of the day.   It doesn’t add to the life of the atrium, in fact it detracts if not occupied.  In addition the effort alone just to set up and knock down everyday for a breakfast buffet must be frustrating.
Thank you for asking and caring.
Joe

Despite my fear of heights, I enjoyed my stay on the seventh floor. The employees were super helpful, and the checkin and checkout process were as seamless as I've ever seen. The hotel is beautiful.

column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;I had to cancel due to the Green Bay Airport being shutdown due to weather. Upon calling just to let you know that I would not be making my stay, the girl on the phone sounded very annoyed that I was bothering her with my call, she was very short, and borderline rude with her attitude. I’ll just note that I did not ask for a refund or anything else, I was simply being courteous and letting the hotel know I couldn’t make it. You never know if it’s all booked up, maybe a walk in could have been accommodated by me calling. Very disappointed in how she handled the situation.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

Thank you for staying with us recently at the Hyatt Regency Green Bay, for being a loyal World of Hyatt member, and for taking the time to complete our guest satisfaction survey regarding your stay. We utlize feedback from guests such as yourself to learn and grow from. It appears, based on your survey, that we fell short of your expectations in multiple aspects of your stay. We will also take your feedback regarding complimentary coffee into consideration. 2020-01-12 07:37:08] Email received from: Tia Label <tialeslie@me.com>: Hi Rob:
Thanks for your note :) I travel constantly, and have stayed at this Hyatt in Green Bay a few times. I understand you probably had people coming in for the Green Bay/Seattle game that Friday but every time I stay, there is hardly a soul in there. With the hundreds of rooms you probably have, and to not extend an extra 30 min check out seemed unfounded. Regarding my dinner salad, I’ve included my receipt and a copy of the pub menu. The $10.50 - crunch salad that I had for dinner, I’m pretty sure was pulled from an ice chest and seemed pre-prepared in it’s cold to the touch container. It’s a shaved cabbage, carrot, cucumber salad with peanuts —there isn’t even a protein on it for $11.08? So with a tip, it was $13.08 which probably cost $1.00 or $2 to make?! Something that wasn’t even warmed or freshly prepared and pulled from a cold bin is poor form. This should have been an $7-$8 dollar salad, at best. I’ve included my receipt and the pub menu. 
The wake-up call was 30 min late. I’m glad I always set my alarm on my phone for back-up. Breakfast is included in most hotels now, and I understand if you don’t have the volume to provide a breakfast each day, that would make sense. But to not at least then have a complimentary coffee area in the morning, which most hotels have (Marriot has it all day long, which is so convenient.) The coffee maker in the rooms are nice, but to only have cream in a powder form in a packet — is unappetizing in 2020. So the only choice it to pay for a coffee in your coffee lounge. And after paying $ $13.00 for a cold shaved cabbage salad, is not inspiring.
Anyway, hope this helps in feedback. On the other hand, there was a very nice girl who checked me in (she was Asian perhaps with short black hair?)….so please extend my thanks!
Please let me know what else you may need!
Thanks Rob,
Tia Label

; ; ;Low water pressure, no cold water in kitchenette, sliding glass door in bedroom leaked, only a cooler instead of a working refrigerator as advertised on the web site, spare blanket was in shreds, took days to warm up, air vent fan was very noisy, negative air pressure brought air in under the door from the atrium which was a fire hazard in our opinion; ; ;Some staff provided exemplary service others were minimally competent.  Too few parking during an event and no spaces set aside for me as a handicapped guest.  The gates and parking ticketing was a nightmare.  Only once did we not require assistance in 5 days.  Only one set if elevators was working and there was no advance warning that the hotel was under renovation.  Our original confirmed reservation through Expedia was cancelled causing us to have to rebook the room and change all of our plane reservations.  There wad no one to help us with our bags even though I had called to say we would be arriving late and only after requesting assistance was a  security guard found to help us to our room.  She was excellent and even went down to the desk to get new room cards for us when neither of the originals opened the door.  the second night my card did not open the door either but the staff member who was helping me as my husband was busy looking for a parking space got me a new card.  On New Year’s Ever when we returned to our room, we found someone had entered it although we had posted a fi not disturb sign and left food on the counter with no explanation.  
Then had to stay up another half hour for room service to come fetch it and receive an explanation; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

Thank you for your honest feedback in our Guest Satisfaction Survey.

I apologize that your experience with us was less than stellar. I want to assure you that I hear your concerns and have already been working with my senior leadership team on ways we can improve. One of those steps, is our refurbishment of our lobby and atrium. Another is that our gates and room locks/keys will be getting replaced this year. 

As for your concerns regarding staffing and assistance with luggage, at this time, our property does not offer bell services. I'm glad that my team was able to have Nichole assist you with luggage and with accessing your room when your keys failed to let you in. I spoke with Noely and Kolton, the Assistant Front Office Managers on my team, and they shared with me that as a goodwill gesture to apologize for the inconveniences you experienced, they sent an amenity to your room. I have spoke with them, as well as our room service team in regards to entering rooms with Do Not Disturb signs. They should have left a note stating that we had something to deliver and a note regarding the amenity sent up. 

I have brought your room concerns to the attention of our Head of Engineering to ensure he is able to get his team set up to inspect the room you were in and repair anything that is out of safety protocols.

If there is anything else you would like to discuss, please do not hesitate to reach out. I hope that you will come back in the future and that our guest experience enhancements make for a better stay.
